== Changelog

=== 1.7.1 (released 09.02.2024)
* bump POI from 5.2.3 to 5.2.5
* upgrade Gradle from 7.x 8.5

=== 1.7.0 (released 22.12.2022)
* bump POI from 5.2.2 to 5.2.3

=== 1.6.0 (released 05.09.2022)
* #4 add matcher doesNotContainText - thanks to Vitali Plagov for PR #4
* upgrade POI 4.1.2 -> 5.2.2
* upgrade from hamcrest-core:1.3 to hamcrest 2.2

=== 1.5.0 (released 03.12.2021)
* #2 fix assertions for floating point numbers  --  thanks to Dmitry Romashov for PR #3

=== 1.4.3 (released 15.06.2020)
* upgrade to POI 4.1.2 and JUnit 4.13

=== 1.4.2 (released 16.08.2019)
* upgrade to POI 4.1.0

=== 1.4.1 (released 27.11.2018)
* upgrade to POI 4.0.0

=== 1.4.0 (released 04.06.2018)
* upgrade to Java 8

=== 1.3 (released 19.02.2018)
* Add XLSX support
* upgrade to POI 3.17
* now all constructors with File, URL or InputStream parameter do throw IOException (instead of wrapping it into IllegalArgumentException)

=== 1.2 (released 12.02.2016)
* add method `assertThat(xls, containsRow("cell 1 text", "cell 2 text", "cell 3 text"));`
* change license to less restrictive MIT

=== 1.1 (released 12.08.2015)
* simplify API: all public methods are in class XLS

=== 1.0 (released 28.06.2015)
* created `xls-test` library with the only function `assertThat(xls, containsText("Some cell text"));`
